Package: PhosphoEnzymes
Title: A Reproducible, Substrate-Aware Reference of Human Kinases and Phosphatases
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Mahmoud", family = "Eladawi",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "eladawimahmoud@tutamail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1383-834X"))
Description: A reproducible reference resource for the human phosphorylation
    machinery: protein kinases and protein phosphatases, assembled from
    multiple expert catalogs and keyed on base Ensembl gene IDs. Enzymes are
    typed by substrate class (protein vs lipid / nucleotide / carbohydrate)
    via a substrate-aware gate that keeps sequence-family membership as evidence
    rather than letting it override substrate (the PI3K / PTEN principle).
    Each gene carries a rigor metric counting distinct evidence classes
    (structural/evolutionary catalog and protein-specific EC) and a practical
    evidence_tier. Built tables ship as package data; the deterministic
    regeneration pipeline lives in inst/scripts. The accessor and term-set
    reader functions use only base R; the optional path that recomputes
    substrate calls under a user-supplied term set draws on dplyr, purrr,
    stringr, and readr, which are therefore Suggests rather than hard
    dependencies. Package code is released under the MIT license; the bundled
    data tables are released under CC BY 4.0, with per-source licenses and
    attribution recorded in inst/extdata/SOURCES.tsv. See the vignette for
    usage.
